MM:
You want to diagree with Shakespeare and with all the Masters?  It's
your prerogative.

The wisest thing we can do is &quot;fear offending God.&quot;  God doesn't look
for excuses to punish us, but if we misuse the human form, he can take
it away.  Look around you.  Do you see the lower species?  Do you see
animals, birds, insects, water creatures, and plants?  Why are they in
that condition, and we are in this better condition?  Answer:  God's
will.  If we look analytically, we will see that humans are a tiny
percentage of all the life on this planet.  Humans are favored.  Who
gave them this favored status?  Answer:  God.  What God has given, he
can take away.  Christ said, &quot;He who ears to hear, let him hear, there
will be wailing and gnashing of teeth.&quot;  The architects of the
Christian Religion tried to edit out all the references to
reincarnation, but somehow, that one survived.  We should take it
seriously.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; If you don't realize by now the love of God, why are you
&gt; even in yoga.
">

MM:
Are you serious?  If there is so much of God's love, then why are we
living in chaos?  It is obviously more of a punishment on earth, than
a paradise.  I think maybe you are living in fantasyland.  Try to look
at everything around you.  You should see that it is not all a
paradise.  People are starving everyday.  Is that the love of God?  Is
it a punishment?  Your contention raises too many questions, while my
contention is more logical.  Go into a prison and tell them about
God's love.  Go into a hospital full of terrminally ill people, and
thell them about God's love.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; That's what yoga is all about, it is to show someone that God
&gt; is to be loved and not feared, in yoga don't have to believe all the
&gt; hearsay, which sounds like Christianity more than Buddhism.
">

MM:
I'm not saying to fear God, himself, but fear offending him.  If you
love someone you won't want to offend them.  That is the principle
behind it.  God is very lenient, very merciful, but if we offend him
too much, he could destroy a city, country, or even the whole planet.
This wholesale destruction has been called a dissolution, or on a
bigger scale, a grand dissolution.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; &quot;best safety lies in fear&quot; to me this would be talking about anything except
&gt; God, because if God is in you and you are in God, then that's where the word
&gt; oneness come from,  there is no fear, you are at one!!
">

MM:
It's not just lip service.  It involves dismantling our ego, and
casting off all sinful habits.  We can't just say, prematurely, I'm
one with God, if we are still sinning everyday.  We should reach his
level, then we will know the difference between right and wrong.

Yoga means to unite.  We can try, with the help of a Master, to unite
with higher levels of consciousness.  God is available to human
beings, if we can qualify.  Living in fantasyland is not the answer.
Facing the reality, that this world is a MIXTURE of rewards and
punishments, will help.  You can call a punishment, love too, but not
many people can do that.  If you could, then you could say that it is
all God's love, even if we are assigned to the plant kingdom.  So, it
depends on how much we can accept God's will, ultimately.

Michael Martin

